  levelName: Pyramid
  startingCodeHint: "-- Goal: Build a yellow pyramid.\r\n-- The size of each layer
    should depend on its height 'y'.\r\n-- The 'size' variable is calculated for
    you.\r\n-- Use it to limit the x and z coordinates.\r\n-- Hint: math.abs() helps
    check both positive and negative sides at once.\r\n\r\nfunction PlaceVoxel(x,
    y, z)\r\n  local color = 0\r\n  local size = 4 - y -- Layer at y=0 has size=4,
    layer at y=1 has size=3...\r\n  \r\n  if y >= 0 and y < 4 then\r\n    -- Change
    this condition to use the 'size' variable!\r\n    color = 4\r\n  end\r\n  \r\n 
    return color\r\nend"
